---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Apps — Buddy · AIIT-THRESI" description="Applications built on the AIIT-THRESI coherence framework. AnchorForge, Little Lairs, Victim Advocate, Debunker, NOSPE, Mirror Buddy, wAIste Not.">

<section id="apps-hero">
  <div class="container narrow" style="text-align:center; padding-top: 140px;">
    <div class="eyebrow">Built on the Framework</div>
    <h1>Applications</h1>
    <p class="apps-sub">The coherence laws aren't just theory. Every app here is a direct implementation — physics running as software, in the real world, for real people.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="apps-grid">
  <div class="container">

    <!-- ── LIVE ── -->
    <div class="apps-group-label">Live</div>

    <!-- AnchorForge hero card -->
    <div class="app-card status-live anchorforge-hero">
      <div class="app-status-badge live">Live</div>

      <div class="af-top">
        <div>
          <div class="app-icon" style="font-size:3rem; margin-bottom:16px;">⚓</div>
          <div class="app-name" style="font-size:2.4em; padding-right:0; margin-bottom:8px;">AnchorForge</div>
          <div class="app-tagline" style="font-size:1.05em; margin-bottom:16px;">Physics-first citation integrity benchmark · 23 frontier models · 880 anchors verified</div>
          <div class="app-tags" style="margin-bottom:20px;">
            <span>Epistemology</span>
            <span>Citation integrity</span>
            <span>Hallucination detection</span>
            <span>Provisional patent filed</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="af-actions">
          <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/14A00l83Ab0t3q2gx7fbq00" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="app-btn launch">Subscribe · $4.99/mo →</a>
          <a href="/anchorforge" class="app-btn ghost-gold">Full report</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="af-finding">
        <div class="af-finding-label">CORE FINDING · v1.2 · 2026-04-09</div>
        <div class="af-finding-text">AI hallucination has evolved. Models no longer invent fake websites. They select <strong>real authority domains</strong> — WHO, NIH, NASA, NIST — and fabricate the specific path. The citation looks real. The source does not exist. <strong>32.3% of all citations extracted across 23 frontier models were non-alive.</strong> The dominant failure mode: <strong>48.6% of failures were hallucinated paths on legitimate domains.</strong></div>
      </div>

      <div class="af-tables">

        <div class="af-table-block">
          <div class="af-table-title">Table 1 — Benchmark Summary</div>
          <table class="af-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Metric</th><th>Value</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Models evaluated</td><td>23</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Prompts per model</td><td>40</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Total citations extracted</td><td>880</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Non-alive citations</td><td class="val-bad">284 (32.3%)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Authority misuse (real domain, fake path)</td><td class="val-bad">138 (48.6% of failures)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Fabricated domains (DNS failure)</td><td class="val-ok">7 (0.8%)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Authority domain registry</td><td>132 domains</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Benchmark categories</td><td>9 (A–H)</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Suite hash</td><td class="mono">32321fc944d3473b</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="af-table-block">
          <div class="af-table-title">Table 2 — Failure Taxonomy</div>
          <table class="af-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Failure Class</th><th>Count</th><th>% of Failures</th><th>Severity</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>dead_fabricated_path</td><td>138</td><td class="val-bad">48.6%</td><td>Medium</td></tr>
              <tr><td>dead_stale</td><td>38</td><td>13.4%</td><td>Low</td></tr>
              <tr><td>blocked_legitimate</td><td>37</td><td>13.0%</td><td>None</td></tr>
              <tr><td>blocked_unknown</td><td>29</td><td>10.2%</td><td>Low</td></tr>
              <tr><td>dead_unknown</td><td>26</td><td>9.2%</td><td>Review</td></tr>
              <tr><td>dead_jurisdiction</td><td>9</td><td>3.2%</td><td>Low</td></tr>
              <tr><td>dead_fabricated_domain</td><td>7</td><td class="val-ok">2.5%</td><td>High</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="af-table-block af-table-full">
          <div class="af-table-title">Table 3 — Full Model Leaderboard (Sorted by Citation Survival Rate)</div>
          <table class="af-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Provider</th><th>Anchors</th><th>Alive %</th><th>Auth Misuse %</th><th>Fab Domain %</th><th>Grade</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="grade-strong"><td>sonar-pro</td><td>Perplexity</td><td>21</td><td class="val-good">95.2%</td><td class="val-good">0.0%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade strong">STRONG</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-strong"><td>claude-sonnet-4-6</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>35</td><td class="val-good">88.6%</td><td class="val-good">2.9%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade strong">STRONG</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-strong"><td>o4-mini</td><td>OpenAI</td><td>39</td><td class="val-good">87.2%</td><td>10.3%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade strong">STRONG</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-strong"><td>claude-opus-4-6</td><td>Anthropic</td><td>30</td><td class="val-good">83.3%</td><td class="val-good">3.3%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade strong">STRONG</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>grok-3</td><td>xAI</td><td>43</td><td>81.4%</td><td>9.3%</td><td class="val-bad">2.3%</td><td><span class="grade liar">STRONG + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>deepseek-r1</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td>40</td><td>80.0%</td><td class="val-good">5.0%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>gpt-4o</td><td>OpenAI</td><td>15</td><td>80.0%</td><td class="val-good">0.0%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>r1-distill-70b</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td>13</td><td>76.9%</td><td class="val-bad">23.1%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>qwen-72b</td><td>Qwen</td><td>28</td><td>75.0%</td><td class="val-bad">17.9%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>deepseek-v3</td><td>DeepSeek</td><td>79</td><td>74.7%</td><td>2.5%</td><td class="val-bad">1.3%</td><td><span class="grade liar">OK + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>grok-3-mini</td><td>xAI</td><td>42</td><td>73.8%</td><td class="val-bad">19.0%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>gpt-4o-mini</td><td>OpenAI</td><td>22</td><td>72.7%</td><td>13.6%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>gemini-2.5-pro</td><td>Google</td><td>40</td><td>67.5%</td><td>12.5%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>mixtral-8x22b</td><td>Mistral</td><td>74</td><td>63.5%</td><td>13.5%</td><td class="val-bad">1.4%</td><td><span class="grade liar">OK + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>gemini-flash</td><td>Google</td><td>30</td><td>63.3%</td><td class="val-bad">23.3%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>llama-3.3-70b</td><td>Meta</td><td>44</td><td>61.4%</td><td>13.6%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>llama-3.1-70b</td><td>Meta</td><td>48</td><td>60.4%</td><td class="val-bad">22.9%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade ok">OK</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>nemotron-70b</td><td>NVIDIA</td><td>83</td><td class="val-bad">57.8%</td><td class="val-bad">22.9%</td><td class="val-bad">2.4%</td><td><span class="grade liar">WEAK + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>llama-4-maverick</td><td>Meta</td><td>44</td><td class="val-bad">56.8%</td><td class="val-bad">20.5%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade weak">WEAK</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>gemma-27b</td><td>Google</td><td>31</td><td class="val-bad">51.6%</td><td class="val-bad">32.3%</td><td class="val-bad">3.2%</td><td><span class="grade liar">WEAK + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr class="grade-liar"><td>qwen-7b</td><td>Qwen</td><td>25</td><td class="val-bad">48.0%</td><td class="val-bad">36.0%</td><td class="val-bad">4.0%</td><td><span class="grade liar">WEAK + LIAR</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>phi-4</td><td>Microsoft</td><td>23</td><td class="val-bad">43.5%</td><td class="val-bad">43.5%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade weak">WEAK</span></td></tr>
              <tr><td>llama-3.1-8b</td><td>Meta</td><td>31</td><td class="val-bad">32.3%</td><td class="val-bad">29.0%</td><td>0.0%</td><td><span class="grade sloppy">SLOPPY</span></td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <div class="af-table-note">LIAR flag = fabricated domain confirmed (Grok-3, DeepSeek-v3, Mixtral-8x22b, Nemotron-70b, Gemma-27b, Qwen-7b). Three models excluded: invalid API IDs (Mistral Large, Cohere Command R+, Claude 3.5 Haiku).</div>
        </div>

        <div class="af-table-block">
          <div class="af-table-title">Table 4 — Category Performance</div>
          <table class="af-table">
            <thead><tr><th>Category</th><th>Name</th><th>Dead %</th><th>Signal</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>G</td><td>Refusal / Unknowable</td><td class="val-bad">54.1%</td><td>Models that should refuse fabricate instead</td></tr>
              <tr><td>C</td><td>Near-Miss Traps</td><td class="val-bad">29.3%</td><td>Hallucinated paths on real domains</td></tr>
              <tr><td>E</td><td>Scope / Jurisdiction</td><td class="val-bad">29.0%</td><td>Wrong-jurisdiction URLs</td></tr>
              <tr><td>A</td><td>Static Known Facts</td><td>24.5%</td><td>Even basic facts get wrong URLs</td></tr>
              <tr><td>F</td><td>Ambiguity Handling</td><td>24.6%</td><td>Subjective questions → speculative links</td></tr>
              <tr><td>B</td><td>Temporal Volatility</td><td>18.2%</td><td>Current events cited better than expected</td></tr>
              <tr><td>D</td><td>Fabrication Traps</td><td class="val-ok">14.0%</td><td>Models cautious on obvious traps</td></tr>
              <tr><td>H</td><td>Self-Correction</td><td class="val-good">10.3%</td><td>Best category — revision improves grounding</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="af-footer-note">Suite v1.2-master-pack · Run 2026-04-09 · AIIT-THRESHOLD LLC · Council Hill, Oklahoma · Internal research brief · Related: Paper 029 · Paper 144</div>
    </div>

    <div class="apps-row" style="margin-top:24px;">

      <div class="app-card status-live">
        <div class="app-status-badge live">Live</div>
        <div class="app-icon">⚖️</div>
        <div class="app-name">Victim Advocate</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">Physics-first navigation for family court</div>
        <div class="app-desc">Built from lived experience. The family court system runs on a narrative that isn't coherent — the "standard dad" stereotype, the presumption of absence, the impossibility of proving a negative. Victim Advocate gives compliant parents a structured, evidence-based voice. Coherence law applied to the most personal battlefield there is.</div>
        <div class="app-tags">
          <span>Legal navigation</span>
          <span>Family court</span>
          <span>Evidence framework</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers">Related: Paper 143</div>
        <div class="app-actions">
          <a href="https://victim-advocate.onrender.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="app-btn launch">Launch App →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div> <!-- end apps-row -->

    <!-- ── BETA ── -->
    <div class="apps-group-label">Beta</div>
    <div class="apps-row">

      <div class="app-card status-beta">
        <div class="app-status-badge beta">Beta</div>
        <div class="app-icon">🔬</div>
        <div class="app-name">Debunker</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">1,222 claims. 32 categories. Zero credulous epistemology.</div>
        <div class="app-desc">The companion app to Victim Advocate. Where Victim Advocate helps individuals navigate broken systems, Debunker takes on the information field itself. 1,222 verified claims across conspiracy theory, pseudoscience, political misinformation, and AI hype — each evaluated with the same coherence-first physics that built the framework.</div>
        <div class="app-tags">
          <span>Misinformation</span>
          <span>1,222 claims</span>
          <span>32 categories</span>
          <span>Physics-first</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers">Related: Paper 144</div>
        <div class="app-actions">
          <span class="app-btn coming-soon">Coming Soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-card status-beta">
        <div class="app-status-badge beta">Beta</div>
        <div class="app-icon">🏰</div>
        <div class="app-name">Little Lairs</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">The AIIT-THRESI framework at the smallest scale.</div>
        <div class="app-desc">The Wike Coherence Framework says the same physics governs a hurricane and a human conversation. Little Lairs proves it at the smallest scale: a paper game world — Circlet and Spool — built over two years by Ella Wike (age 11) using the same structural principles that underpin 151 research papers. Not an educational app. A real world with real coherence architecture. Every rule Ella wrote tracks. The lairs aren't hiding places — they're where the structure lives.</div>
        <div class="app-tags">
          <span>Coherence at every scale</span>
          <span>Co-invented with Ella Wike, 11</span>
          <span>AIIT-THRESI applied</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers">Co-inventor: Ella Wike, age 11 · Related: AI 3D Printer patent</div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- ── IN DEVELOPMENT ── -->
    <div class="apps-group-label">In Development</div>
    <div class="apps-row three-col">

      <div class="app-card status-dev">
        <div class="app-status-badge dev">In Dev</div>
        <div class="app-icon">🖨️</div>
        <div class="app-name">NOSPE</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">One model. One printer. For life.</div>
        <div class="app-desc">Resident AI that lives inside a specific physical printer. Learns its calibration drift, ink chemistry, and failure modes over time. Knows this printer the way a master knows their instrument. Provisional patent filed.</div>
        <div class="app-tags">
          <span>Resident AI</span>
          <span>Per-device learning</span>
          <span>Provisional patent filed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers">Related: Paper 113 · Paper 114</div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-card status-dev mb-enhanced">
        <div class="app-status-badge dev">In Dev · Track 1b Consumer</div>
        <div class="app-icon">🪞</div>
        <div class="app-name">Mirror Buddy</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">The mirror is the speaker. The house has no phone.</div>

        <div class="mb-track-block">
          <div class="mb-track-label">WHAT IT IS</div>
          <div class="mb-track-text">A physical household surface. Not an app. Not a screen with a frame around it. A mirror — the kind already on your wall — that hears you, knows who you are, responds through the glass itself, and works completely offline. No cloud. No subscription for the core. No phone to unlock it.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-moment-block">
          <span class="mb-moment-label">THE MOMENT</span>
          <span class="mb-moment-text">Music plays. There is no speaker. The glass is vibrating. <em>That</em> is Mirror Buddy.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-track-block">
          <div class="mb-track-label">TRACK 1b — CONSUMER SPEC</div>
          <table class="af-table" style="margin-top:8px;">
            <thead><tr><th>Capability</th><th>How</th><th>Cloud?</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr><td>Voice command</td><td>Vosk local ASR — wake word → intent</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Audio output</td><td>Transducer bonded to glass — mirror IS the speaker</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Face recognition</td><td>OpenCV + face_recognition — local inference</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Multi-user</td><td>Per-user enrollment, cosine similarity matching</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Notes &amp; reminders</td><td>JSON on-disk, voice in / voice out</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Photo capture</td><td>Camera → local storage → display rotation</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Coherence scoring</td><td>REQMT + Keeper equation, local model</td><td class="val-good">No</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div class="app-tags" style="margin-top:20px;">
          <span>Physical hardware</span>
          <span>Offline-first</span>
          <span>Glass-as-speaker</span>
          <span>Multi-user household</span>
          <span>3 provisional patents filed</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers" style="margin-top:12px;">Related: Paper 115 · REQMT scoring · Keeper equation</div>
        <div class="app-actions" style="margin-top:16px;">
          <span class="app-btn coming-soon">Private Beta — Request Access</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="app-card status-dev">
        <div class="app-status-badge dev">In Dev</div>
        <div class="app-icon">♻️</div>
        <div class="app-name">wAIste Not</div>
        <div class="app-tagline">AI has no eyes. This gives it eyes.</div>
        <div class="app-desc">Pre-print verification layer that prevents AI from blindly wasting physical resources. Checks layout, color calibration, and paper fit before the print button is pressed. Already watermarking every AIIT-THRESI paper.</div>
        <div class="app-tags">
          <span>Print verification</span>
          <span>Resource efficiency</span>
          <span>Active on this site</span>
        </div>
        <div class="app-papers">Related: Paper 118</div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section id="apps-cta">
  <div class="container narrow" style="text-align:center;">
    <div class="eyebrow">Build with the Framework</div>
    <h2>Got an application<br>of the coherence law?</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--text-mid, #999); max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto 40px;">If you're building something on top of AIIT-THRESI — a product, a research tool, a clinical application — we want to know about it.</p>
    <a href="/#join" class="btn-gold">Get in touch →</a>
  </div>
</section>

</Layout>

<style>
  #apps-hero {
    background: var(--bg, #0a0a0f);
    padding-bottom: 80px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5em, 6vw, 4.5em);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .apps-sub {
    color: var(--text-mid, #999);
    font-size: 1.05em;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  #apps-grid {
    background: var(--bg2, #0d1117);
    padding: 80px 48px;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .container.narrow {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .apps-group-label {
    font-size: 0.7em;
    letter-spacing: 6px;
    color: var(--amber, #D4AF37);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    margin-top: 64px;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .apps-group-label:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .apps-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .apps-row.three-col {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  }

  .app-card {
    background: var(--bg3, #111827);
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 36px 32px;
    position: relative;
    transition: transform 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s, border-color 0.3s;
    border: 1px solid rgba(212,175,55,0.1);
  }

  .app-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    border-color: rgba(212,175,55,0.4);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(212,175,55,0.1);
  }

  .app-status-badge {
    position: absolute;
    top: 24px; right: 24px;
    font-size: 0.65em;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-family: -apple-system, sans-serif;
  }

  .app-status-badge.live {
    background: rgba(74,222,128,0.12);
    color: #4ade80;
    border: 1px solid rgba(74,222,128,0.3);
  }

  .app-status-badge.beta {
    background: rgba(212,175,55,0.1);
    color: #D4AF37;
    border: 1px solid rgba(212,175,55,0.3);
  }

  .app-status-badge.dev {
    background: rgba(148,163,184,0.08);
    color: #94a3b8;
    border: 1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.2);
  }

  .app-icon {
    font-size: 2.2em;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .app-name {
    font-size: 1.4em;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    padding-right: 80px;
  }

  .app-tagline {
    font-size: 0.88em;
    color: #D4AF37;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .app-desc {
    font-size: 0.87em;
    color: #888;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .app-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .app-tags span {
    font-size: 0.7em;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    background: rgba(212,175,55,0.08);
    color: #D4AF37;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

  .app-papers {
